What you need to know:

Other value-added products she makes under her business name Broad Range Enterprise are roasted cashew nuts, peanut butter, millet, rice, cassava and roasted peanut flour.From her savings, she bought a roaster that processes 20 kilos of cereals and nuts at a go at Sh90,000, a peanut miller at Sh90,000, a weighing scale at Sh4,500 and a sealing machine at Sh2,500.Stella sells her products through a network of friends, retailers and bakeries, with a kilo of dried simsim going for Sh250 to Sh300.To get the certification, she made an application, then a Kebs officer visited her premises – her house, from where she does the production – and checked the processing, from the start to the end of packaging.